                            <comment id="475079" author="yujian" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2025 19:17:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;conf-sanity test 30a passed on master client with b2_15 server interop testing:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/210e604d-6ef6-4eb2-bbcf-a2fd9cdd1d9f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/210e604d-6ef6-4eb2-bbcf-a2fd9cdd1d9f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="474379" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2025 08:30:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Emoly Liu &amp;lt;emoly@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61730&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61730&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18336&quot; title=&quot;interop: conf-sanity test_30a: FAIL: Deleted value=64 -ne orig=61&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18336&quot;&gt;LU-18336&lt;/a&gt; tests: restore max_read_ahead_whole_mb correctly&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 128535b15b55e24a1613c18405a3ce09464294b1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="474376" author="emoly.liu" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2025 08:19:42 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It looks like the problem here is that conf-sanity test_28A is setting&#160;&lt;tt&gt;llite.*.max_read_ahead_whole_mb=&lt;em&gt;DEFAULT&lt;/em&gt;&#160;- 3&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;and this is kept in the config log. Then, when this parameter is deleted during test_30a the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;orig&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; value is 3 less than the new (real default) value.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, you are right. The &quot;orig&quot; value is changed and never be restored correctly when $max &amp;lt;= $orig in conf-sanity.sh test_28A, which causes test_30a failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="462701" author="adilger" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2025 20:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like the problem here is that conf-sanity test_28A is setting &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_whole_mb=&lt;em&gt;DEFAULT&lt;/em&gt; &amp;#45; 3&lt;/tt&gt; and this is kept in the config log.  Then, when this parameter is deleted during test_30a the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;orig&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; value is 3 less than the new (real default) value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know why this (mostly) happens in interop testing.  There is code in b_es6_0 &lt;tt&gt;test-framework.sh::init_compression()&lt;/tt&gt; that may be changing &lt;tt&gt;PERM_CMD=&quot;$LCTL set_param -P&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; from the default &lt;tt&gt;PERM_CMD=&quot;$LCTL conf_param&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; (on both master and b_es6_0), but this test is also failing with master-next:b2_15 and master-next:b2_16 interop testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the right solution here is to delete any default setting for &lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.max_read_ahead_whole_mb&lt;/tt&gt; at the start of the test (for both &lt;tt&gt;set_param -P&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;conf_param&lt;/tt&gt;) and remount the client before assuming that the current value is the default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="433052" author="yujian" created="Mon, 28 Oct 2024 21:39:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.16.0 RC5 client with 2.15.5 server:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/5bf51531-c7ba-462d-aecb-d01083f98aba&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/5bf51531-c7ba-462d-aecb-d01083f98aba&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431308" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2024 05:47:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an old issue, more than 2.5 years. I suspect it is related to the previous test case failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="431242" author="lixi_wc" created="Sat, 12 Oct 2024 14:23:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emoly.liu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emoly.liu&quot;&gt;emoly.liu&lt;/a&gt; Would you please take a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="430958" author="yujian" created="Thu, 10 Oct 2024 17:57:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failure occurred consistently in the following 2.16.0 clients with 2.15.5 servers interop test sessions:&lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el8.10-x86_64_full-dne-part-3 &lt;br/&gt;
lustre-reviews_el8.10-x86_64_el9.4-x86_64_full-dne-part-3 &lt;br/&gt;
